rdf:Description.lla:note: Place of birth on other documents down as 'New Quay'.
Date of discharge from this ship also down as '1868-01-08' on Form R.V. 18
At the end of the voyage, there was a document stating that 'there was no person by the name of 'Evan Jones' on board of this vessel: it is John Jones.'
In Capacity column, there is also 'Only 20188'.
Previous ship more likely to be 'Ann & Mary'.
Surname down as 'Landow' and 'Lander' on other documents
Ship in which he last served looks like 'Iron Queen', but no ship of that name registered In Aberayron
